<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// have a great way to detect when this happens.  As an approximation, we</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (e.g. DCE&#39;ing an indirect call and duplicating an unrelated block with a</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (NumIndirectRemoved &gt; NumIndirectAdded &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><span class="doxyHighlight">        NumDirectRemoved &lt; NumDirectAdded)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// After scanning this function, if we still have entries in callsites, then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// they are dangling pointers.  WeakTrackingVH should save us for this, so</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="516"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// functions in this SCC.  However, we support iterative compilation in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00517" /><CodeLine lineNumber="517"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// case where a function pass devirtualizes a call to a function.  For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00518" /><CodeLine lineNumber="518"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// example, it is very common for a function pass (often GVN or instcombine)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00520" /><CodeLine lineNumber="520"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// information, we would like the call to be an inline candidate, infer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00521" /><CodeLine lineNumber="521"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// mod-ref information etc.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="522"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00523" /><CodeLine lineNumber="523"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Because of this, we allow iteration up to a specified iteration count.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00524" /><CodeLine lineNumber="524"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This only happens in the case of a devirtualized call, so we only burn</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00525" /><CodeLine lineNumber="525"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// compile time in the case that we&#39;re making progress.  We also have a hard</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00526" /><CodeLine lineNumber="526"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// iteration count limit in case there is crazy code.</span></CodeLine>
